gard to the wing bars, as the closely related southern beardless tyrannulet, C. obsoletum, with which it was once considered conspecific. However, the two forms overlap without interbreeding in Costa Rica. Northern beardless tyrannulets are active birds, feeding in a vireo or warbler-like fashion on insects, spiders and berries. The call is a loud whistled Fleeeeeerrr, sometimes broken up as a fleeer-it, or a flee-flee-flee-flee. In courtship, or when alarmed, the crests are raised, the tail flicked, and an excited call is made. References Stiles, F. Gary; Alexander Frank Skutch (1989). A Guide to the Birds of Costa Rica. Cornell University Press. ISBN 978-0-8014-9600-4. External links Northern beardless tyrannulet Images http://tsuru-bird.net/image.htm Copyright 2009 Monte M. Taylor", "shortSummary": "The northern beardless tyrannulet (Camptostoma imberbe) is a small passerine bird in the tyrant flycatcher family. It breeds from southeast…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f4/Northern_Beardless-Tyrannulet_%2818560065092%29.jpg/960px-Northern_Beardless-Tyrannulet_%2818560065092%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-camptostoma", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-camptostoma-imberbe", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-camptostoma", "species": "taxonomy-species-camptostoma-imberbe"}, "expandable": true, "x": 573.75, "y": 183.5, "z": 518.96}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-camptostoma-imberbe", "name": "Northern beardless tyrannulet", "latinName": "Camptostoma imberbe", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Northern beardless tyrannulet（Camptostoma imberbe）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Northern beardless tyrannulet。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": 573.75, "y": 183.5, "z": 525.97}], "links